## `test_fuse_symlink_and_readlink(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fsym-2 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary -->

### Postconditions

```python
(mount / "target").write_bytes(b"hi")
os.symlink("/target", mount / "link")

# readlink returns bytes matching what we stored.
assert os.readlink(mount / "link") == "/target"
```

---

## `test_fuse_follow_symlink_on_open(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fsym-3 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary -->

### Postconditions

```python
(mount / "target").write_bytes(b"hello")
os.symlink(str(mount / "target"), mount / "link")

# Opening the symlink transparently follows to the target (default).
with open(mount / "link", "rb") as f:
    assert f.read() == b"hello"
```

---

## `test_fuse_lstat_vs_stat(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fsym-4 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary -->

### Postconditions

```python
(mount / "target").write_bytes(b"hello")
os.symlink(str(mount / "target"), mount / "link")

# stat follows the symlink; lstat does not.
st = os.stat(mount / "link")
lst = os.lstat(mount / "link")
assert st.st_ino != lst.st_ino
```

---

## `test_fuse_dangling_symlink_lstat_ok_stat_enoent(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fsym-5 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary + errno mapping -->

### Postconditions

```python
os.symlink("/does/not/exist", mount / "dangling")

# lstat succeeds on the link itself.
lst = os.lstat(mount / "dangling")
import stat
assert stat.S_ISLNK(lst.st_mode)

# stat (which follows) errors with ENOENT.
with pytest.raises(FileNotFoundError) as e:
    os.stat(mount / "dangling")
assert e.value.errno == errno.ENOENT
```

---

## `test_fuse_unlink_symlink(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fsym-6 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary -->

### Postconditions

```python
(mount / "target").write_bytes(b"x")
os.symlink(str(mount / "target"), mount / "link")

os.unlink(mount / "link")
# link gone, target still present.
assert not (mount / "link").exists()
assert (mount / "target").read_bytes() == b"x"
```

---

## `test_fuse_symlink_chain_eloop(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fsym-7 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary + kernel ELOOP behavior -->

### Purpose
A chain of more than `MAXSYMLINKS` (40 on Linux) symlinks raises `OSError(errno=ELOOP)` at the kernel layer. Our adapter must surface the right errno for this to trigger kernel ELOOP behavior as expected.

### Postconditions

```python
os.symlink("/link0", mount / "link0")   # self-cycle of length 1
with pytest.raises(OSError) as e:
    os.stat(mount / "link0")
assert e.value.errno == errno.ELOOP
```

---

## `test_fuse_symlink_survives_rename(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fsym-8 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary -->

### Postconditions

```python
os.symlink("/target/does/not/exist", mount / "link")
os.rename(mount / "link", mount / "relocated")
assert os.readlink(mount / "relocated") == "/target/does/not/exist"
```

